phrases: I tried to copy the clothing worn by humans in this era.
Did I get this outfit wrong?
Should I find something more tailored for male tastes?
By the way, why are you here?
Why cannot I be in your room?
How come the cat's okay, but not me?
I guess telling you that I want my privacy probably will not work.
You were not like this before.
You are asking me to remember old times?
That is a very human thing to request.
It does not make sense to tell you about yourself, though.
You are really telling me you came from a place beneath this country?
And I came from a place that is basically the opposite side.
Would not the people on the other side fall off?
The people on the other side wonder why you do not fall off.
You tell such interesting stories, Kohaku.
Okay, how about that for the countries on the other side,
the stars are in different positions?
He had a real thirst for knowledge.
You told somebody from the Heian period that the Earth is round?
You seemed so interested in the stars, though!
I guess for now we can assume he is harmless.
And we cannot go trying anything on a god of calamity.
He is less like a god and more like a NEET.
Who knows what goes through his head?
It is a waste of time to try and figure out what a typhoon's thinking.
Well, we will just have to keep an eye on him.
And it is valuable data, too.
Theo-kun, Sakaki-kun, can you turn those in?
The things you turn in every year.
It is that time of the year already?
Shinjuku Ward Special Cases Fixed-Point Observation.
Unsolved Missing Girl Cases in Tokyo
It is a pain in the ass, you know?
All right, we are heading outside today.
We need to observe six Anothers that have permanent residency here
and report that there is no issues.
It is tradition for the Nocturnal Community Relations Section.
Our job is to make sure they are doing well.
We had a big catch today!
We are just having a nice drink.
It is that Ears of Sand guy!
He is no different than any other human.
we have always been drinking with the same group, and it is getting boring.
Here, let me pour you one.
What, too good to drink our sake?
Sorry, I am still on the job.
Do not put your lips on anything an Another offers you.
They were just being nice, though...
Anothers are not nice or not nice.
It is possible that they needed you to drink before they could consume you.
They just spend the whole year drinking there.
But we do not know for sure that they will always be there.
Checking on them is part of our job.
But how did they know about the Ears of Sand?
Now, just sign some paperwork to show you got it.
It is a piece of cake!
They moved a little from before.
All the time you spend on this really helps us out.
I am stationed at a police box.
Your kids have grown up, huh?
That is a good thing, having a family.
May 23rd Shinjuku Ward Kabukicho Abandoned Building
Can that Haguro-san guy see Anothers?
I have never heard of him being able to talk to them like you, though.
He is harmless, but sometimes he changes locations, and it is a pain.
Nothing new there, so let us go.
We have four left to check today.
Hey, what happened to number one on the list?
They were around before World War II,
and were the boss of this area, kind of.
They were from the ward office, right?
May 23rd Shinjuku Ward Kabukicho Discount Outlet
There is number Three, Minerva's Owl.
Well, she is set down roots and cannot move.
And there is number five, Mezu.
May 24th Shinjuku Ward Kabukicho Movie Theater Plaza
May 24th Shinjuku Ward Kabukicho Batting Center
What is a hyena doing in Shinjuku?
He came over with the US Army after the war, and stayed here.
So you are the Ears of Sand, huh?
That was a police officer he was carrying.
This is what they call a kamikakushi, a random disappearance.
That police officer will not be coming back unless we save him.
Their eyes met, and he was taken away.
You need to follow a certain set of steps to enter.
Sounds like a pain to do every time.
That is Kabukicho's Kio Inari shrine?
He is using a place like that as his base?
Another number one, the one who disappeared!
Why did he come back now?
More importantly, how do we save Haguro-san?
The Another does not seem to be in a hurry.
We cannot do much with him right in front of us.
The Ears of Sand guy's right here!
I found out that Another's name.
Is not that the god of this shrine?
I never thought I would see you again.
This is probably going to be another thorn in my side...
The Ears of Sand guy's upset!
So, Seimei, what do you want from me?
Please give us back that person, Haguro-san.
He needs to stay here with me.
I just drank a little too much and fell asleep.
Now that I am awake, we need to throw a festival.
D-Do not tell me you want him as a sacrifice?
He just needs to stay here and drink with me.
For a hundred years or so.
Miyako, what are you two talking about?
He says he wants to drink sake with Haguro-san for a hundred years.
That sounds just like an Another.
From his family's perspective, that is the same as him dying!
Is it that big a problem?
Then will you take him back by force?
Why did you piss him off?
Let us have a drinking party, then!
Would not it be better to have a festival with more people?
Why not have a drinking contest with the three of them, then?
And if they win, you give the man back.
Hey, do not just decide that!
At times like these, do not you save everybody and go back with everybody?
This time you are abandoning him?
Well... we are having a drinking contest, and if we win, he will give Haguro-san back.
Hang on, you are agreeing to a contest with something that size?!
I cannot think of another way.
Miyako, tell him you accept as long as it is something humans can drink.
We do not have a choice.
It is worse than I thought.
If I help you, it is not fair.
I will take on as many as you want.
Miyako, call Senda-san and have him send reinforcements.
I will keep going until then.
Um... I am going to the bathroom.
What, you are going to call for help?
The last one seems like he is still got some fight in him.
I have been running for 20 minutes and yet...
What is with that damn face?
You think you are so great just because you can drink a little...
Try being a host for once, asshole.
Dealing with a bunch of stuck-up bitches all day...
And it is a pain in the ass for me, you know!
We will have to start over tomorrow.
By then the alcohol will wear off.
I cannot get drunk off the cheap stuff.
You are such a spoiled bastard.
Hey, it is the Ears of Sand dude.
You hung in there, but you are just a human in the end.
Having a drink now that you have woken up?
You should have told us to join you!
Alcohol makes the world go round!
Let us all just get drunk!
Now the party's started for real.
Time for me to join in.
I want to go home and take a bath.
Told you there would be trouble.
